relevant_findings.general: A middle aged female in no acute distress.
relevant_findings.HEENT: Pupils 4mm and reactive to light, no pharyngeal erythemia, mucous membranes moist, no lymphadenopathy.
relevant_findings.chest: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, no wheezes, no crackles, no ronchi.
relevant_findings.cardiovascular: S1 S2 Normal in quality and intensity, regular rate and rhythm, no murmurs, rubs or gallops.
relevant_findings.abdomen: Peritoneal catheter in place, no erythemia, distended, tense, tender to palpation in the epigastrium, resonant to percussion, no left lower quadrant pain.
relevant_findings.extremities: Warm, well perfused, very dry skin, no clubbing, cyanosis or edema, dorsalis pedis pulses 2+.
relevant_findings.neurological: Alert, oriented to person, place, and time, cranial nerves grossly intact, moving all extremities.
